cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with autoregressive models (ARMs) for image and audio data, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for sampling from ARMs, which involves forecasting modules and fixed-point iteration, indicating a potential fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to explicit likelihood modeling and discrete latent modeling, suggesting a possible fit for cs.CL (Computation and Language).
